article.headline: Akron 76, Eastern Michigan 68
article.story: AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- Bubba Walther hit two 3-pointers to key an 18-0 first-half run and help Akron to a 76-68 win over Eastern Michigan on Saturday night. Darryl Peterson scored 16 points, Rick McFadden came off the bench for 15 and Romeo Travis had 12 for the Zips (9-5, 3-3 Mid-American Conference). Darryl Garrett, who scored 13 points for Eastern Michigan (9-6, 3-3), hit a 3-pointer at the 6:14 mark of the first half to tie the game at 20. The Eagles didn't score again until Garrett hit another shot behind the arc at the 1:02 mark. Walther, who totaled eight points, touched off the 18-point spurt with a 3 and after Peterson hit two layups, Walther's second 3-pointer made it 30-20. Dru Joyce scored on a drive before Travis and McFadden each hit shots behind the arc to push the lead to 38-20. The lead never dropped below 10 points again until the final minute of the game. Michael Ross had 22 points and Markus Austin 14 for Eastern Michigan, which was outrebounded 35-24.
